1.notes:
Check out the video!
At the beginning of each phase of this program, we've recorded a primer to help you know what to expect and to give some bits of advice and wisdom. Make sure to give it a watch.

2.notes: Ignore the (deadlift) - this is a regular pull-up. Use a band or a foot for assistance if necessary. If that's not an option, lat pulldowns are just fine!

3.notes: If you're already a highbar squatter, either try low bar here, or use SSB or Front Squat.
Soft, controlled touch on the chest!

4.notes: This will default to your deadlift 1RM if you've never done this exercise before. Refer to RPE, then use the E1RM button after you've completed the first set to correct for the rest of the block.
A superset made up of front/lateral/rear delt raises in that order. Reps given are reps per arm.

5.notes: Preferred exercises are planks, rotations, landmine work, McGill exercises, ab wheel

IMPORTANT!!!: Alright, if you're using this to prepare for a meet or max test, then you'll complete this week! If not, you can just cut this week out,deload your program for one or two, and either loop this program, or move on to another one
The taper week should be run like this - D1 - 5-7 days out from the competition D3 - 2-4 days out from the competition
